	(text "Notes: \n* This project is still under development.\n* Capacitor values are suggestions and are not critical. Use X7R or COG.\n* The schematic and layout include redundant 50k and 80k resistors\n  as options - only use 1, obviously. \n* The 100k resistors are optional, used if found necessary.\n* Zero ohm resistors may substitute for ferrite beads. \n* Operation of the inverter and flip-flop may be 3.3V down to 2.5V \n  with appropriate part selection (parts shown are for 3.3V). "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 195.326 268.224 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "52776a0f-0bbb-475d-8ea3-12f4bd2c4d64")
	)
	(text "NU180 - A Drop-in Replacement for the 3458A's U180 Hybrid. \nV.1.0 by Zondar, DB4UCH, MiDi, Wanghar, Kleinstein and others."
